headline: The Dow Is on Track for a Record. Why It's Beating the S&P, Nasdaq.
summary: The Dow is on track for its twelfth record close of the year.  The blue-chip index was up 341 points, or 0.7%, and on track to set a fresh closing high.  It was also on track to close north of the 47,000 mark for the first time on record, according to Dow Jones Market Data.
